            ">Netanyahu meets Trump</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/netanyahu-trump-white-house-press-conference-east-room.png" alt="Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and US President Donald Trump speak during a joint press conference in the East Room of the White House" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and US President Donald Trump speak during a joint press conference in the East Room of the White House. Credits: The White House, via Wikipedia
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">President Trump welcomed Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu outside the West Wing before meeting in the Oval Office. Their discussion addressed a spectrum of issues, including the sweeping tariffs (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-08-04-2025-h1-1-see-video" target="_blank">see video</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Netanyahu pledged to reduce Israel’s $7.4B trade deficit with the US, hoping to abstain from the sweeping tariffs. Trump noted that the US provides $4B in annual aid, mostly military. Therefore, even if Israel reduces its trade deficit, it may not escape the 17% tariff. The two also discussed efforts to secure a ceasefire in Gaza. Trump said freeing hostages remains a top priority, while Netanyahu expressed support for a hostage agreement and said operations in Gaza would continue.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">On Iran, Trump confirmed that the US is pursuing direct talks to halt its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-08-04-2025-h1-2-nuclear-program" target="_blank">nuclear program</a>. Iran, however, insisted on indirect negotiations. The US president also assured that he would work on Israel-Turkey tensions after Israeli officials raised concerns about Turkish influence in Damascus and called for demilitarization in the south.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
