          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">80th anniversary of Buchenwald
        </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/alojzy-maciak-buchenwald-liberation-80th-anniversary-commemoration-germany.png" alt="Holocaust survivor Alojzy Maciak from Poland attends the commemoration ceremony to mark the 80th anniversary of the liberation of the Buchenwald Nazi concentration camp at the camp's memorial site in Buchenwald, near Weimar, eastern Germany" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Holocaust survivor Alojzy Maciak from Poland attends the commemoration ceremony to mark the 80th anniversary of the liberation of the Buchenwald Nazi concentration camp at the camp's memorial site in Buchenwald, near Weimar, eastern Germany. Credits: JENS SCHLUETER / AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
      
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Buchenwald was one of the largest concentration camps in Nazi Germany. It was built in 1937 (before the start of World War II) near Weimar and held around 280,000 people over eight years. Many died from forced labor, starvation, disease, or brutal experiments. On April 11, 1945, in expectation of liberation, Buchenwald prisoners took control of the camp, with US forces finally coming later that afternoon.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Germany held a memorial in Weimar to mark <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-08-04-2025-h2-3-80-years-since-that-day" target="_blank">80 years since that day</a>, and several Holocaust survivors attended the event. Former German President Christian Wulff warned that the far-right’s rise in Europe echoes the conditions that once allowed such camps to exist. He criticized the AfD’s anti-immigrant stance and called for a stronger defense of democracy.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The event witnessed a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-08-04-2025-h2-4-hiccup-in-its-rundown" target="_blank">hiccup in its rundown</a> to the ceremony when the Israeli officials objected to the speech by philosopher Omri Boehm, grandson of a Holocaust survivor and a critic of the Israeli government.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
