              border-left: 3px solid #4D3060;
              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>A false tweet from an account named Walter Bloomberg caused $10 trillion worth of market fluctuation</strong>. The tweet, citing Reuters and CNBC, claimed Trump was considering a 90-day tariff pause, causing market volatility. The White House quickly denied it, sharing a Fox News clip to clarify. Reuters and CNBC admitted errors, highlighting the dangers of rapid, unverified news dissemination in global markets (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-08-04-2025-br3-9-read-more" target="_blank">read more</a>).</p>
