              padding-left: 14px;
              margin-bottom: 15px;
                    "><strong>Trump has ordered a fresh national security review of Nippon Steel’s bid to acquire US Steel</strong>, raising hopes for approval after Biden blocked the agreement. Both companies have sued, citing political bias in Biden’s decision. The renewed review paused litigation until June 5, and US Steel shares surged nearly 14% following <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-08-04-2025-br5-11-white-house-announcement" target="_blank">the announcement</a>.</p>
